data.text:
Hugh Keays-Byrne (18 May 1947 â€“ 2 December 2020) was a British-Australian actor. He began his career on stage in his native England, where he was member of the Royal Shakespeare Company between 1968 and 1972. After emigrating to Australia in 1973, he established himself as a supporting actor in action and thriller films like Stone and The Man from Hong Kong. His breakthrough film role was as the antagonist Toecutter in the original Mad Max.[1] Decades later, he played another villain in the series, Immortan Joe in Mad Max: Fury Road.[1]
